    <note>Gao(1) Bing [918] Di's [926] son. XCB, 290.2b-3a, 296.11a, 303.14b, 304.13b, 310.11a; SHY:ZG, 66.13b. According to Chao(2) Buzhi's [13] funerary inscription for Bing's son, Yuanchang [13513], Bing's first wife was surname Chao(2). Yuanchang was recommended by his waijia, Chao(2) Zongque [8001]. Zongque's cousin, Zongke [7121] (q.v.), was the father-in-law of a Gao(1) Yuanzhen [13174], who is probably Yuanchang's brother or cousin. If generational logic holds true, the father-in-law of Bing was a member of a Chao(2) in the generation before Zongque and Zongke and since the immediate reference was to Zongque, I am assuming that it was his father, Jiong [3012].</note>
